commitResults.messageBody:
The build.gradle file is outdated. In addition, there is no need
for the main and run methods in the current Duke class since we are
more focus on the GUI.

Updating build.gradle allows shadowJar to build a compatible jar
file for javaFx and updating Duke.java will improve code quality
via removable of dead code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions to Ui.java and other Command java class files
commitResults.messageBody:
Assertions allows duke to terminate in the case of a possible bug,
and sooner the execution stops, the safer it is.

Multiple checks for null in the parameters passed into Ui.java and
the string response returned from command execution.

By checking for null will allow us to verify and ensure that the
program is behaving as expected.

Presence of dead code such as welcomeResponse() and lineResponse() in
Duke.java and unclear prominent path in certain classes.

Remove the dead code and introduce guard clauses into our program.

Removing dead code as we can simply recover it from revision control
tool when we need it in the future and use of guard clause in some code
will help us to make the code more reader friendly.

Removing Storage test cases as it is difficult to test Storage without
proper stub and introducing additional test cases for ToDo and Unmark
command to improve unit testing of Duke.

Testing todo toStringForStorage method as well as Unmark's constructor
and isExit status.

This will ensure that the test cases closely test the program for bugs.
